On Thu, 18 Feb 1999, Gregory Maxwell wrote:
> So it seems to me the issue would be solved by allocating the dma buffer
> at module load then loading the modules at boot.
The issue would be solved completely by reserving some small portion of
ram (as a percentage of total ram) under 16mb as 'dma ram'. Of course
configurable as a kernel boot variable.
